        <detaileddescription>
<para>Generic function to send object data stored in U to Ughost according to communication pattern</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>is</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>the Kokkos::View type. It must be Kokkos::LayoutLeft </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>distributed_dim</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>position distributed objects index coordinate in U(..,..,...). When distributed object index is not the leftmost index (distributed_dim != DataArray_t::rank-1), packing/unpacking is less efficient because data needs to be transposed. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>U</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>a view containing data distributed accross the distributed_dim-th dimension. Must be in accordance with the communication pattern. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Ughost</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>A view to recieve the exchanged objects. This must be allocated to have <ref refid="classdyablo_1_1ViewCommunicator_1a0d2dac0199f6b71455c74aad75e5c254" kindref="member">getNumGhosts()</ref> elements in the distributed_dim-th dimension, and must have the same shape than U in all other dimensions </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
